{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "11", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "18", "M": "42", "S": "02"}}, "news": [{"title": "Ulhasnagar civic body identifies \u20b9170 crore in tax linked to non-existent or wrongly recorded properties", "para": "Ulhasnagar Municipal Corporation launched 'Project Manthan' to clean its property tax database.  This initiative identified nearly Rs 170 crore in unrealizable property tax dues.  The project uncovered ghost and duplicate properties, and wrongly assessed mobile towers.  UMC staff delivered property tax bills, updating owner contact details efficiently.  This data cleaning aims for a transparent and reliable property tax system.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/ulhasnagar-municipal-corporation-uncovers-170-crore-in-overdue-property-tax-from-ghost-properties/132324768?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1251338/132324768.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Navi Mumbai civic body issues notices to 295 officials over illegal constructions", "para": "Navi Mumbai Municipal Corporation issued notices to 295 officials for illegal constructions.  These notices cover deputy and assistant municipal commissioners and clerical staff.  Cidco has been made a party to the legal proceedings before the Bombay High Court.  The civic body has razed a portion of unauthorized structures since June.  Disciplinary actions will follow after explanations are received from the concerned individuals.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/navi-mumbai-municipal-corporation-takes-action-against-295-officials-for-illegal-constructions/132324756?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-119687/132324756.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Residents protest over waterlogging, unfinished amenities at Zirakpur housing society", "para": "Residents of Aura Homes near Nabha Sahib protested against persistent waterlogging and lack of civic infrastructure. They claim the builder abandoned the project after selling most of the units. Promised facilities like a clubhouse and park remain incomplete despite assurances over three years. Residents urged authorities to inspect the project and ensure amenities are finished. The builder stated that 90% of the project is sold and committed to addressing grievances.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/zirakpur-residents-rally-against-builder-over-waterlogging-and-incomplete-amenities/132324741?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-190144/132324741.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}